and made &quot;one-hot encoding&quot; And for each position has a column.</p><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">- For the “Traits” column we have detected that each player can have more than</p><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">one trait, it can be useful, detrimental or useless, so we applied &quot;one-hot</p><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">encoding&quot; on the column then combined them in one full of zeroes by adding “1”</p><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">if the trait is useful, subtracting “1” if its detrimental, neglect it if it is useless.</p><h2 style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">-Plusing Data:</h2><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">We have checked each column that has integers and ‘+’ between them to add</p><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">them.</p><h2 style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 17pt;text-align: left;">-Filling The Missing Values:</h2><p style="padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">For each missing value in the column, we have filled it by the mean of that column.</p></li><li data-list-text=""><h1 style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 42pt;text-indent: -18pt;text-align: left;">Applying Correlation</h1><p style="padding-top: 9pt;padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">We considered the features that have a correlation value greater than 70%.</p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><br/></p><p style="padding-left: 64pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;"><span><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><img width="481" height="305" src="data:image/jpg;base64,"/></td></tr></table></span></p></li><li data-list-text=""><h1 style="padding-top: 2pt;padding-left: 42pt;text-indent: -18pt;text-align: left;">Regression Techniques</h1><h2 style="padding-top: 9pt;padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;text-align: left;">-multiple regression:</h2><p style="padding-top: 9pt;padding-left: 24pt;text-indent: 0pt;line-height: 107%;text-align: left;">We have split the data into 30% test and 70% training set.
